      <memberdef kind="slot" id="class_preferences_keyboard_tab_1adddddc79c491a6b00ca506423ef85cb2" prot="private" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>bool</type>
        <definition>bool PreferencesKeyboardTab::refine_shortcut_list</definition>
        <argsstring>(const QString &amp;s, QTreeWidgetItem *parent=nullptr)</argsstring>
        <name>refine_shortcut_list</name>
        <param>
          <type>const QString &amp;</type>
          <declname>s</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>QTreeWidgetItem *</type>
          <declname>parent</declname>
          <defval>nullptr</defval>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Shows/hides shortcut entries according to a shortcut query. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function can be directly connected to QLineEdit::textChanged() for simplicity.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>s</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The search query to compare shortcut names to.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>parent</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>This is used as the function calls itself recursively to traverse the menu item hierarchy. This should be left as nullptr when called externally.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para></para>
</simplesect>
Value used as function calls itself recursively to determine if a menu parent has any children that are not hidden. If so, TRUE is returned so the parent is shown too (even if it doesn&apos;t match the search query). If not, FALSE is returned so the parent is hidden. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
