      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_preferences_keyboard_tab_1ad059ba43418582748b70c682d2ea0f94" prot="private" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void PreferencesKeyboardTab::setup_kbd_shortcut_worker</definition>
        <argsstring>(QMenu *menu, QTreeWidgetItem *parent)</argsstring>
        <name>setup_kbd_shortcut_worker</name>
        <param>
          <type>QMenu *</type>
          <declname>menu</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>QTreeWidgetItem *</type>
          <declname>parent</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Internal function called by <ref refid="class_preferences_keyboard_tab_1a9a4a3aec7ccbbc71044e7f3abb672146" kindref="member">setup_kbd_shortcuts()</ref> to traverse down the menu bar&apos;s hierarchy and populate the shortcut panel. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function will call itself recursively as it finds submenus belong to the menu provided. It will also create QTreeWidgetItems as children of the parent item provided, either using them as parents themselves for submenus or attaching a <ref refid="class_key_sequence_editor" kindref="compound">KeySequenceEditor</ref> to them for shortcut editing.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>menu</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The current menu to traverse down.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>parent</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The parent item to add QTreeWidgetItems to. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
